---
import MainLayout from "@layouts/MainLayout.astro"
import { Image } from "astro:assets"
import { SITE_TITLE } from "src/consts"
import Seo from "@components/seo/Seo.astro"

import assets_images_blueprint_for_scrum_team_success_BlueprintForScrumTeamSuccessBookCover_800x1280_1_640x1024_jpg from "@assets/images/blueprint-for-scrum-team-success/BlueprintForScrumTeamSuccessBookCover-800x1280-1-640x1024.jpg"

const wpId = 15856
const title = "Blueprint for Effective Scrum"
const description =
	"Do you relate to these comments in your work and Scrum team? Our ScrumMaster is also our Project Manager ... they're still behaving like the person in charge. I hate Scrum because I spend all of my time in meetings. I'm frustrated with our Scrum team's Product Backlog Refinement... our Product Owner doesn't have clear ..."
const status = "publish"
const type = "page"
const createdAt = new Date("2023-12-19T14:04:32")
const modifiedAt = new Date("2024-05-13T20:30:17")
const author = "heather-uhlagilepainrelief-com"
---

<MainLayout>
	<Seo slot="head" seo={{ title, description }} options={{ brand: SITE_TITLE }} />
	<p>Do you relate to these comments in your work and Scrum team?</p>
	<ul>
		<li>
			Our ScrumMaster is also our Project Manager … they’re still behaving like the person in
			charge.
		</li>
		<li>I hate Scrum because I spend all of my time in meetings.</li>
		<li>
			I’m frustrated with our Scrum team’s Product Backlog Refinement… our Product Owner doesn’t
			have clear priorities.
		</li>
		<li>Our Scrum Sprint Planning really bogs down … it’s a huge waste of time.</li>
		<li>
			My development team wastes a lot of time estimating user stories that we don&#8217;t
			understand.
		</li>
		<li>
			Our Product Owner is bad at maintaining realistic scope for our product… it’s challenging to
			deliver.
		</li>
		<li>Sprint Reviews are boring… we almost fall asleep.</li>
		<li>
			I&#8217;m frustrated that our Product Owner doesn&#8217;t have a clear vision of the product
			we&#8217;re trying to build.
		</li>
		<li>
			Scrum Sprint Retrospectives call for improvements but they never get made… so why do we bother
			to hold them?
		</li>
		<li>Our ScrumMaster is also our Product Owner… is that right? I’m confused.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		<Image
			decoding="async"
			alt="Blueprint For Scrum Team Success  by Agile Pain Relief"
			width="640"
			height="1024"
			sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px"
			src={assets_images_blueprint_for_scrum_team_success_BlueprintForScrumTeamSuccessBookCover_800x1280_1_640x1024_jpg}
			widths={[640, 188, 768, 800]}
		/>
	</p>
	<p>
		If you’ve experienced any of the above, then our upcoming release of the <em
			>Blueprint for Effective Scrum</em
		> will help you and your team get to the next level of Scrum and remove the confusion and guesswork.
	</p>
	<p>Subscribe to be alerted when it’s ready for beta testing.</p>
	<hr />
	<style>
		#drip-ef-778389433 {
			font: 1rem/1.5rem sans-serif;
			width: 100%;
		}
